properties.areaDesc: Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 to 60 NM; Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20 to 60 NM
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 5 at 3:33AM EST until February 6 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds around 20 kt
with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 4 to 6 feet expected. For the
Gale Watch, south winds around 25 kt with frequent gusts of 35
to 40 kt and seas up to 11 feet possible.

* WHERE...Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20
to 60 NM and Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20
to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM to 1 PM EST
Thursday. For the Gale Watch, from Thursday 1 PM EST through
late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.
